code: library(readMVT) library(shiny) library(leaflet) home <- c(-71.6995, 42.1349)  # center of Massachusetts zoom <- 8                     # starting zoom level (shows all of Massachusetts) data.zoom <- 14   # all MVT tiles are read at this zoom level to simplify caching trigger <- 14     # show vector data when zoomed in this far or more zoom.levels = 14:22    # show vector data at these zoom levels xml <- read.XML('https://umassdsl.webgis1.com/geoserver')   # get capabilities of our GeoServer streamlines <- layer.info(xml, 'testbed:streamlines')       # get info for stream linework culverts <- layer.info(xml, 'testbed:CL_crossings7')        # get info for crossing points > streamlines $layer [1] "testbed_streamlines"  $box [1] -73.58043  41.22166 -69.89367  42.95567  $tiles    zoom    rowmin    rowmax    colmin    colmax 1     0         0         0         0         0 2     1         0         0         0         0 3     2         1         1         1         1 4     3         2         2         2         2 5     4         5         5         4         4 6     5        11        11         9         9 7     6        23        23        18        19 8     7        47        47        37        39 9     8        94        95        75        78 10    9       188       191       151       156 11   10       376       383       302       313 12   11       752       766       605       626   ... 31   30 394726401 401696265 317408725 328404932  $url [1] https://umassdsl.webgis1.com/geoserver/gwc/service/wmts/rest/testbed:streamlines/simple_streams/EPSG:900913/EPSG:900913:{zoom}/{TileRow}/{TileCol}?format=application/vnd.mapbox-vector-tile

text: Now ’re ready guts example. display Leaflet basemap set initial viewport. ESRI World Street Map makes good basemap example, streams match vector streams. Everything interesting happens inside [leaflet::observe()]. First, display zoom level left sidebar, “TRIGGERED!” zoom level trigger. expect see streams crossings TRIGGERED shown. ’re zoomed trigger zoom, ’re done–basemap displayed, none vector data. ’re zoomed (equal ) trigger, ’ll read vector tiles render . use [leaflet::leafletProxy()] modify current display ’s unnecessary (ugly) redrawing. get corner tiles current viewport fixed tile zoom level Leaflet. Now read vector tiles streams viewport, omitting ’ve already rendered. Rendering captured session$userData[[layername]]. Initially, NULL, read.viewport.tiles initialize . don’t want avoid redrawing, can omit argument following line saves . vector data viewport haven’t yet rendered, addPolylines renders streams. thing culverts. Note move culverts separate -clause different trigger wanted . call [leaflet::groupOptions()]] displays previously-rendered vector data selected zoom levels. Without , zooming show streams culverts tiles ’ve visited, visible tiles. ugly. hiding vector data, smoothly vanish zoom . Leaflet map returned rendered [shiny::observe()] finishes.
code: server <- function(input, output, session) { output$map <- renderLeaflet({    leaflet() |>       addProviderTiles(providers$Esri.WorldStreetMap) |>       setView(lng = home[1], lat = home[2], zoom = zoom) }) observe({    output$dashboard <- renderUI({       output$dashboard <- renderUI({          tagList(div('zoom = ', input$map_zoom,),                  div(strong(if(isTRUE(input$map_zoom >= trigger)) ' TRIGGERED!')))       })    }) if(isTRUE(input$map_zoom >= trigger)) {   # if above trigger zoom, draw features    m <- leafletProxy('map', session) nw <- get.tile(data.zoom, input$map_bounds$north, input$map_bounds$west)   # corners of viewport se <- get.tile(data.zoom, input$map_bounds$south, input$map_bounds$east) x <- read.viewport.tiles(streamlines, nw, se, data.zoom, session$userData[[streamlines$layer]]) session$userData[[streamlines$layer]] <- x$drawn if(!is.null(x$tiles))    m <- addPolylines(m, data = x$tiles, group = 'vector', opacity = 0.4, color = 'cornflowerblue', weight = 3) x <- read.viewport.tiles(culverts, nw, se, data.zoom, session$userData[[culverts$layer]]) session$userData[[culverts$layer]] <- x$drawn if(!is.null(x$tiles))    m <- addCircleMarkers(m, data = x$tiles, group = 'vector', opacity = 1, color = 'orange', radius = 4) return(groupOptions(m, 'vector', zoomLevels = zoom.levels))       }    }) }  shinyApp(ui, server)

title: shiny-example
text: ’re using RStudio, able install named packages, copy code, paste script window, save , click “Run App.”
code: library(readMVT) library(shiny) library(leaflet)  home <- c(-71.6995, 42.1349)  # center of Massachusetts zoom <- 8                     # starting zoom level (shows all of Massachusetts)  data.zoom <- 14               # all MVT tiles are read at this zoom level to simplify caching trigger <- 14                 # show vector data when zoomed in this far or more zoom.levels = 14:22           # show vector data at these zoom levels  xml <- read.XML('https://umassdsl.webgis1.com/geoserver')   # get capabilities of our GeoServer streamlines <- layer.info(xml, 'testbed:streamlines')       # get info for stream linework culverts <- layer.info(xml, 'testbed:CL_crossings7')        # get info for crossing points   # User interface --------------------- ui <- fluidPage(    fluidRow(       column(2,              wellPanel(                 uiOutput('dashboard')              )       ),       column(10,              leafletOutput('map', height = '80vh')       )) )   # Server ----------------------------- server <- function(input, output, session) {      output$map <- renderLeaflet({       leaflet() |>          addProviderTiles(providers$Esri.WorldStreetMap) |>          setView(lng = home[1], lat = home[2], zoom = zoom)    })     observe({       output$dashboard <- renderUI({          output$dashboard <- renderUI({             tagList(div('zoom = ', input$map_zoom,),                     div(strong(if(isTRUE(input$map_zoom >= trigger)) ' TRIGGERED!')))          })       })        if(isTRUE(input$map_zoom >= trigger)) {   # if above trigger zoom, draw features          m <- leafletProxy('map', session)                    nw <- get.tile(data.zoom, input$map_bounds$north, input$map_bounds$west)   # corners of viewport          se <- get.tile(data.zoom, input$map_bounds$south, input$map_bounds$east)           x <- read.viewport.tiles(streamlines, nw, se, data.zoom, session$userData[[streamlines$layer]])          session$userData[[streamlines$layer]] <- x$drawn          if(!is.null(x$tiles))             m <- addPolylines(m, data = x$tiles, group = 'vector', opacity = 0.4, color = 'cornflowerblue', weight = 3)           x <- read.viewport.tiles(culverts, nw, se, data.zoom, session$userData[[culverts$layer]])          session$userData[[culverts$layer]] <- x$drawn          if(!is.null(x$tiles))             m <- addCircleMarkers(m, data = x$tiles, group = 'vector', opacity = 1, color = 'orange', radius = 4)           return(groupOptions(m, 'vector', zoomLevels = zoom.levels))       }    }) }  shinyApp(ui, server)
